  "text": "A second pattern of results that we observed across all datasets was that SC was less variable than FC across subjects. There were fewer significant eigenvalues for the SC compared to the FC (See Table S3 ). From the figures (Panel A in Figures 3-8 ), the knee, or drop-off in the variance explained by subsequent PCs [CITATION_1] was evidently sharper for the SC than the FC. Thus, although the common component was dominant for both modalities, the second and later components explained a larger portion of variance in the FC than in the SC.",
